frameDefinitions: A Perpetrator (generally intentionally) commits a Crime, i.e. does something not permitted by the laws of society.
A Wrongdoer engages in a Misdeed.
An Agent performs some Action which is considered imprudent.
This frame contains general words for Individuals, i.e. humans, whose specific acts or general behavior is evaluated against standards of morality or rightness.
In this frame an Offense is described in terms of the legal or other punishing action that can be taken in response to the offense. '
frameExamples: They <t>perpetrated</t> a felony by substituting a lie for negotiations.
You have <t>sinned</t> for the last time, Stephen!
Columbus: Was he a Hero or a <t>Villain</t>?
listRoleDefinitions: An act, generally intentional, that has been formally forbidden by law.
This is the person whose <fen>Misdeed</fen> is being judged with respect to its morality.
The assessment of the <fen>Wrongdoer</fen> is based on his or her <fen>Misdeed</fen>.
The time at which a <fen>Misdeed</fen> is performed.
The individual that performs the <fen>Action</fen>, resulting in danger to themself.
This role denotes the <fen>Action</fen> taken by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> dares to perform the <fen>Action</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> risks doing the <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Offense</fen> is the action, crime, or event which is described in terms of what legal or punishing action can be taken against the offender.
listRoleExamples: How can <fex>he</fex> commit treason against the King of England in a foreign country , if he is not English?
How can he commit <fex>treason</fex> against the King of England in a foreign country , if he is not English?
A murder perpetrated <fex>at 1:08AM this morning</fex> was not investigated until noon today.
We have jurisdiction over crimes committed <fex>in Woodside County</fex>.
The misdeeds <fex>of the previous evening</fex> were all forgotten now.
Sexual peccadilloes <fex>in the White House</fex> are one thing, lying before Congress quite another.
I do n't think <fex>you</fex> should hazard the ascent in the dark , that 's all .
<fex>At dawn</fex>, the Captain chanced opening the hatch.
<fex>Back in his room</fex>, he risked peeking inside.
